column10: A database class that actually spends it's time on databases. CPSC 350 is really a web development course covering websites backed by databases. Yes, you learn about databases in the process, but it's really only as a support topic for the main goal of building the website. A new database course should be created that only focuses on database things (i.e. SQL in depth, schema design, optimizing search algorithms, efficient data storage, etc.) Basically the skills you need as a DBA.
